FBIS4-37647 "drnes121_p_94001" FBIS-NES-94-121 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Rabbani Announces Condition for Herat Talks Rabbani Announces Condition for Herat Talks LD2106175994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106175994 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Persian BFN [Text] Afghan President Borhanoddin Rabbani has announced that he would take part in the Herat talks only on the condition that all leaders of Afghanistan's jihadi parties attend these talks. According to a Central News Unit report from Kabul, Rabbani read out his political statement in Kabul today and asked for convention of a greater national assembly tasked with appointing the president and other key governmental posts.
